LevitateOS License Information
===============================

This project contains multiple components with different licenses:


1. LEVITATEOS RUST CODE (installer/, recipe/, xtask/)
----------------------------------
License: MIT
Copyright (c) 2024-2026 LevitateOS Contributors

The Rust source code (installer, levitate, recipe parser) is MIT licensed.
See LICENSES/MIT.txt for the full license text.


2. SMOLLM3-3B MODEL (vendor/models/)
------------------------------------
License: Apache-2.0
Copyright (c) 2025 Hugging Face

The SmolLM3-3B language model used for the AI installer is Apache 2.0 licensed.
See LICENSES/Apache-2.0.txt for the full license text.
Source: https://huggingface.co/HuggingFaceTB/SmolLM3-3B


3. FEDORA BASE SYSTEM
---------------------
When you build an ISO, the resulting image contains Fedora packages
under various licenses:

  - Linux kernel           : GPL-2.0-only
  - systemd                : LGPL-2.1-or-later
  - GNU coreutils          : GPL-3.0-or-later
  - bash                   : GPL-3.0-or-later
  - util-linux             : GPL-2.0-or-later
  - NetworkManager         : GPL-2.0-or-later
  - GRUB2                  : GPL-3.0-or-later

The GPL-licensed components require source availability when distributing.
Fedora provides source packages at https://src.fedoraproject.org


4. WEBSITE (website/)
---------------------
License: MIT
The documentation website is MIT licensed.


5. DISTRIBUTION NOTICE
----------------------
If you distribute LevitateOS images, you must:

  a) Include this LICENSE file or equivalent notices
  b) Provide access to source code for GPL/LGPL components
  c) Preserve copyright notices

Fedora source packages: https://src.fedoraproject.org
SmolLM3 source: https://huggingface.co/HuggingFaceTB/SmolLM3-3B


6. FULL LICENSE TEXTS
---------------------
See the LICENSES/ directory:
  - LICENSES/MIT.txt          (LevitateOS code, website)
  - LICENSES/Apache-2.0.txt   (SmolLM3 model)
  - LICENSES/GPL-2.0.txt      (Linux kernel, util-linux)
  - LICENSES/GPL-3.0.txt      (coreutils, bash, GRUB2)
  - LICENSES/LGPL-2.1.txt     (systemd)
